<div class="header">
    <h1>BioWave™ NeuroHaptic™ Study</h1>
    <p>Conducted by the Georgia Research Institute of Wellness Technologies*</p>
</div>

<div class="container">

    <h2>Objective</h2>
    <p>To evaluate the effectiveness of NeuroHaptic™ and Predictive HRV Technology in reducing stress levels during high-pressure academic tasks.</p>

    <h2>Method</h2>
    <p>45 college participants (ages 18–24) performed timed cognitive tasks. Stress responses were recorded via HRV comparison during baseline vs. wearable intervention.</p>

    <div class="highlight">
        <strong>Result:</strong> Participants demonstrated an average HRV improvement of <strong>22% within 3 minutes</strong> of BioWave™ activation.
    </div>

    <div class="graph">Graph Placeholder — HRV Increase with NeuroHaptic™</div>

    <h2>Conclusion</h2>
    <p>BioWave™ provided measurable autonomic nervous system stabilization and faster recovery from acute stress triggers.</p>

    <p style="font-size: 12px; color: #777;">
    *This is a development study for R&D purposes, not yet peer-reviewed.
    </p>

